22/* A gmon.out file consists of a header (defined by gmon_hdr) followed
23 by a sequence of records. Each record starts with a one-byte tag
24 identifying the type of records, followed by records specific data. */
25#ifndef gmon_out_h
26#define gmon_out_h
27
28#define GMON_MAGIC "gmon" /* magic cookie */
29#define GMON_VERSION 1 /* version number */
30
31/* Raw header as it appears on file (without padding). */
32struct gmon_hdr
33 {
34 char cookie[4];
35 char version[4];
36 char spare[3 * 4];
37 };
38
39/* Types of records in this file. */
40typedef enum
41 {
42 GMON_TAG_TIME_HIST = 0, GMON_TAG_CG_ARC = 1, GMON_TAG_BB_COUNT = 2
43 }
44GMON_Record_Tag;
45
46#endif /* gmon_out_h */
